//Synovia focal- I describe


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'Yes' radio button from 'Contrast enhanced' box in Page 03
And	I'm on Page 08 - Soft parts of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Synovia focal' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'I describe' radio button is enabled
And 'I know' radio button is enabled

And 'Intracapsular' radio button is enabled
And 'Extracapsular' radio button is enabled
And 'Intrasynovial' radio button is enabled
And 'Extrasynovial' radio button is enabled

And 'Signal T1w' slide bar is enabled
And 'Signal T2w' slide bar is enabled
And 'Blooming artifact'
And 'None' radio button is enabled
And 'Weak' radio button is enabled
And 'Strong' radio button is enabled

And 'Multilobulated' radio button is enabled
And 'Synovial nodulus' radio button is enabled
And 'Synovial proliferations' radio button is enabled

And 'Necrosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Loose body' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bony erosions (insertion of synovial membrane)' checkbox is enabled

And 'Diffuse' radio button is enabled
And 'Focal' radio button is enabled

And 'Differential diagnosis 1' dropdown menu is enabled
And 'Haemarthros' checkbox is enabled
And 'Joint effusion' checkbox is enabled


When I select all 4 parts on the localizer
Then all 4 parts are selected and turn red

When I select 'Synovial nodulus' radio button
Then '> 1 lesions' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Loose body' checkbox
Then '> 1 lesions' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Focal' radio button
Then 'Hoffa Fat body' radio button is enabled
And 'Suprapatellar recess' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Synovial haemangioma' from 'Differential diagnosis 1' dropdown menu
Then 'Differential diagnosis 2' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Synovial chondromatosis' from 'Differential diagnosis 2' dropdown menu
Then 'Secondary' checkbox is enabled
